# Front backlog analysis

## Headline

At `2026-07-14T17:21:25.600Z`, a full metadata-only traversal found **15,061 distinct open conversations** across 151 pages. Front's `_total` said **15,062** at the start of that traversal, so the honest snapshot is **15,061 enumerated / 15,062 reported**; the one-conversation gap is live-search drift, not a hidden estimate. **Only 3,490 were touched in the last 30 days, while 5,945 were older than 90 days.**

The conservative domain/tag classifier found **2,309 notifications** and **653 newsletters**. Removing those two non-overlapping cohorts would take the enumerated backlog from **15,061 to 12,099**. The remaining 12,099 are *unclassified*, not proven live: the available metadata cannot safely distinguish people, stale resolved work, bounces, or auto-replies without reading finer-grained identity/header data.

## Method and privacy boundary

- Read-only source: `GET /conversations/search/is:open`, paged to exhaustion at 100 rows per page.
- Enumerated metadata: conversation ID for in-memory deduplication, last activity timestamp, inbox membership, tags, status, and sender domain derived in memory from Front's recipient handle.
- Persisted here: counts, timestamps, inbox labels, tag names, and domains only.
- Never called a conversation, message, or body endpoint. Never read or persisted a subject, body, customer name, full email address, or message header.
- The traversal changed while it ran: `_total=15,062`, enumerated distinct rows `15,061`. Treat all counts as one timestamped operational snapshot, not transactional truth.

## Age shape

The exclusive buckets add to 15,061.

| Last touched | Exclusive count | Cumulative count |
| --- | ---: | ---: |
| 0-24 hours | 23 | 23 |
| >24 hours-7 days | 777 | 800 |
| >7-30 days | 2,690 | 3,490 |
| >30-90 days | 5,626 | 9,116 |
| >90 days | 5,945 | 5,945 older than 90 days |

This is mostly an old backlog: **76.8% (11,571)** is older than 30 days. Activity is much smaller than the scary all-time number: 23 touched in 24 hours, 800 in 7 days, and 3,490 in 30 days.

## Inbox shape

The six workspace inbox totals were queried separately with `is:open inbox:<id>` at `2026-07-14T17:21:38.600Z`.

| Normalized inbox label | Open |
| --- | ---: |
| Personal Gmail | 8,429 |
| egghead mailbox | 5,466 |
| badass.dev mailbox | 1,382 |
| other small inbox | 19 |
| Skill Recordings | 0 |
| LinkedIn | 0 |

These memberships overlap. Their sum is 15,296, not the unique total; do not add them when rendering system health. The separate 40-product/channel catalog had one open conversation in one channel and zero in the other 39, so it does not explain the 15k backlog.

## Tag shape

Tag counts overlap because a conversation may have multiple tags.

| Tag | Open conversations |
| --- | ---: |
| `Inbox` | 15,061 |
| `emberwave` | 7 |
| `cwa` | 1 |
| `MEGA.dev` | 1 |

Tags are not currently rich enough to classify the backlog. Every open conversation carries `Inbox`; only nine conversations have an additional listed tag.

